steps.prompt:
You are a licensed customs broker preparing a formal customs entry declaration package.

Shipment reference: {{shipment_ref}}
Importer: {{importer_name}} (Tax ID: {{importer_tax_id}})
Port of entry: {{port_of_entry}}
Original shipping documents: {{steps.fetch-shipping-documents.output}}
HS code classifications: {{steps.classify-hs-codes.output.line_item_classifications}}
Duty calculations: {{steps.calculate-duties.output}}

Prepare the complete customs declaration package with the following labeled sections:
- entry_type: the appropriate CBP entry type (e.g., Type 01 Formal Entry, Type 11 Informal Entry) based on shipment value
- entry_summary: structured summary of all line items, HS codes, quantities, values, duty rates, and calculated duty amounts
- importer_of_record: formatted importer details block
- supporting_documents_checklist: list of documents attached and required for this entry type
- total_duties_payable_usd: total of all duty and fee amounts from the duty calculation
- broker_notes: any special handling instructions, free trade agreement applicability, or first sale valuation notes

Format as a professional customs entry package ready for portal submission.

